<p>Spotted <a href="http://conda.pydata.org/docs/index.html">Conda</a> package manager. It handles python installations, in addition to package management. There's also a package index provided by <a href="https://binstar.org/">Binstar</a>. Installed <a href="http://conda.pydata.org/miniconda.html">Miniconda</a>, the bare bones Conda environment.</p>
<p>Can't find a python package in Binstar? Here's a post on <a href="http://www.peterbronez.com/Using%2520PyPi%2520Packages%2520with%2520Conda">Using PyPi Packages with Conda</a>. If that fails, you can try pip from your Conda python environment.</p>
